  "prompt": "What is the best way to remove rust from bike parts?",
  "response": "Here are several effective methods to remove rust from bike parts:\n\n1. Vinegar Method\n- Soak rusty parts in white vinegar\n- Let sit for 24 hours\n- Scrub with steel wool or wire brush\n- Rinse and dry thoroughly\n\n2. Baking Soda Method\n- Make a paste with baking soda and water\n- Apply to rusty areas\n- Let sit for a few hours\n- Scrub with a wire brush\n- Rinse and dry\n\n3. Commercial Rust Removers\n- Use specialized chemical rust removers\n- Follow product instructions carefully\n- Often very effective and quick\n\n4. Electrolysis\n- Use a battery charger and washing soda solution\n- Immerse rusty part in solution\n- Attach to negative terminal\n- Highly effective but requires more setup\n\n5. Mechanical Removal\n- Use steel wool or sandpaper\n- Manually scrub rust away\n- Good for smaller areas\n\n6. Citric Acid Solution\n- Mix citric acid with water\n- Soak parts\n- Scrub and rinse\n- Less harsh than some chemical methods\n\nAfter removing rust, always dry parts completely and apply lubricant or protective coating to prevent future rusting.\n\nChoose method based on part material and rust severity.",
